					</app>-->
					          <app loc="1">
						            <lem>-pasādakanaṁ</lem>
						            <note>On similar uses of forms derived from <foreign>pra-sad</foreign> in the context of conversion of countries, see <bibl>
                        <ptr target="eiad-bibl:Skilling1993"/>: <citedRange>168, n. 13</citedRange>
                     </bibl>; <bibl>
						                  <ptr target="eiad-bibl:Cousins2001"/>:
							<citedRange>141, n. 23</citedRange>
					                </bibl>.</note>
					          </app>
					          <app loc="2">
						            <lem>-navaṁgaṁsathusasana</lem>
						            <note>On the ninefold division of scriptures, specific to Pāli textual transmission and that of several Mahāsāṅghika groups, see <bibl>
                        <ptr target="eiad-bibl:Tournier2017"/>:
							<citedRange>45, n. 186</citedRange>
					                </bibl> and the references quoted there.</note>
					          </app>
				        </listApp>
